---
<SiteLayout site="siliconbased" title="Gravel Calculator: Find Exact Yards & Tons" description="Stop guessing how much gravel you need. Our exact formula calculates cubic yards, cubic meters, and tons instantly. The third factor might surprise you..." canonical="https://siliconbased.dev/gravel-calculator" schema={schema}>
  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="hero">
      <h1>Gravel Calculator</h1>
      <p class="subtitle">Instantly calculate the cubic yards and tons of gravel needed for your project.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="calculator-container">
      <div class="calc-grid">
        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="length">Length</label>
          <div class="input-with-unit">
            <input type="number" id="length" min="0" step="any" placeholder="e.g. 20" value="20" />
            <select id="lengthUnit">
              <option value="ft">Feet (ft)</option>
              <option value="m">Meters (m)</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div class="error-msg" id="lengthError">Please enter a valid length.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="width">Width</label>
          <div class="input-with-unit">
            <input type="number" id="width" min="0" step="any" placeholder="e.g. 10" value="10" />
            <select id="widthUnit">
              <option value="ft">Feet (ft)</option>
              <option value="m">Meters (m)</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div class="error-msg" id="widthError">Please enter a valid width.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="depth">Depth</label>
          <div class="input-with-unit">
            <input type="number" id="depth" min="0" step="any" placeholder="e.g. 4" value="4" />
            <select id="depthUnit">
              <option value="in">Inches (in)</option>
              <option value="cm">Centimeters (cm)</option>
              <option value="ft">Feet (ft)</option>
              <option value="m">Meters (m)</option>
            </select>
          </div>
          <div class="error-msg" id="depthError">Please enter a valid depth.</div>
        </div>

        <div class="input-group">
          <label for="materialType">Material Density</label>
          <select id="materialType">
            <option value="1.4">Standard Gravel / Crushed Stone (1.4 tons/yd³)</option>
            <option value="1.3">Pea Gravel (1.3 tons/yd³)</option>
            <option value="1.5">Crusher Run / Dense Base (1.5 tons/yd³)</option>
            <option value="1.2">Sand / Dry (1.2 tons/yd³)</option>
            <option value="1.1">Mulch / Bark (Approx 0.3 - 0.5 tons/yd³, custom 1.1)</option>
          </select>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="results-area">
        <div class="result-card primary-result">
          <div class="result-label">Volume (Cubic Yards)</div>
          <div class="result-value" id="volumeYards">--</div>
        </div>
        <div class="result-card primary-result">
          <div class="result-label">Estimated Weight (Tons)</div>
          <div class="result-value" id="weightTons">--</div>
        </div>

        <div class="secondary-results">
           <div class="result-card small-result">
            <div class="result-label">Volume (Cubic Meters)</div>
            <div class="result-value-sm" id="volumeMeters">--</div>
          </div>
          <div class="result-card small-result">
            <div class="result-label">Weight (Kilograms)</div>
            <div class="result-value-sm" id="weightKg">--</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="explainer">
      <h2>How to Use the Gravel Calculator</h2>
      <p>Whether you are planning a new driveway, laying a foundation, building a patio base, or simply adding decorative rock to a garden bed, calculating the right amount of gravel is crucial. Ordering too little means pausing your project to await another delivery, while ordering too much wastes both money and labor. This tool instantly converts your measurements into cubic yards and tons—the standard units used by landscaping suppliers.</p>

      <h3>Understanding the Formula</h3>
      <p>The mathematics behind estimating gravel volume involves finding the cubic volume of your area and then converting it to the industry-standard measurement of cubic yards. Most projects are measured with length and width in feet, while depth is often measured in inches.</p>

      <p>The standard formula for volume in cubic yards is:</p>
      <div class="formula-box">
        <code>Volume (yd³) = (Length (ft) × Width (ft) × [Depth (in) ÷ 12]) ÷ 27</code>
      </div>

      <p>Let's break down why this formula works:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Convert Depth to Feet:</strong> Since length and width are in feet, the depth must also be in feet to calculate cubic feet. Dividing inches by 12 achieves this.</li>
        <li><strong>Calculate Cubic Feet:</strong> Multiplying the length (ft) by width (ft) by depth (ft) gives you the total volume in cubic feet.</li>
        <li><strong>Convert to Cubic Yards:</strong> There are 27 cubic feet in one cubic yard (3 feet × 3 feet × 3 feet). Dividing the total cubic feet by 27 gives you the volume in cubic yards.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Estimating the Weight (Tons)</h3>
      <p>Suppliers often sell bulk materials by weight (tons) rather than volume (cubic yards), especially for larger orders. To convert cubic yards to tons, you must account for the density of the specific material.</p>

      <p>The formula for converting yards to tons is:</p>
      <div class="formula-box">
        <code>Weight (Tons) = Volume (yd³) × Material Density (Tons/yd³)</code>
      </div>

      <p>Different materials have different densities:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Standard Gravel or Crushed Stone:</strong> Approximately 1.4 tons per cubic yard. This is the most common multiplier used for general estimations.</li>
        <li><strong>Pea Gravel:</strong> Slightly lighter, averaging around 1.3 tons per cubic yard due to its smooth, rounded shape creating more void space.</li>
        <li><strong>Crusher Run / Dense-Graded Aggregate:</strong> Heavier, often around 1.5 tons per cubic yard. It contains a mix of crushed stone and stone dust, which compacts tightly, reducing void space and increasing density.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>How Deep Should Your Gravel Be?</h3>
      <p>The required depth of your gravel layer dictates the total volume needed. While the ideal depth varies by project and subsoil conditions, here are general guidelines:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Pathways and Walkways:</strong> 2 to 3 inches is typically sufficient for foot traffic.</li>
        <li><strong>Patios:</strong> 4 inches is recommended as a solid base beneath pavers or concrete.</li>
        <li><strong>Driveways:</strong> 4 to 6 inches is the standard for a compacted base capable of supporting everyday passenger vehicles.</li>
        <li><strong>Heavy-Duty Areas:</strong> 8 to 12 inches may be necessary for parking pads supporting RVs, heavy trucks, or heavy machinery.</li>
      </ul>

      <h3>Accounting for Compaction and Waste</h3>
      <p>When you order gravel, it arrives loose. As you spread and tamp (or roll) the material, it compacts. Crusher run, for example, is specifically designed to interlock and compact into a hard surface. Because of this compaction, a loose cubic yard will yield slightly less than a compacted cubic yard.</p>
      <p>Furthermore, some material is inevitably lost during transport, spreading, or settling into the subgrade. For these reasons, industry professionals typically recommend ordering an additional <strong>5% to 10%</strong> over your exact calculated requirement. This buffer ensures you have enough material to achieve your desired final, compacted depth.</p>

      <p>Need to calculate proportional changes for your budget or project scaling? Check out our <a href="/percent-change-calculator">Percent Change Calculator</a>.</p>
    </div>

    <section class="faq-section">
      <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>How much gravel do I need for a driveway?</summary>
        <p>For a standard driveway, you generally need a depth of 4 to 6 inches of gravel over a solid base. First, multiply the length and width of the driveway in feet to find the square footage. Then, multiply that by the depth (converted to feet by dividing inches by 12) to get the volume in cubic feet. Divide by 27 to find cubic yards. Finally, multiply by 1.4 to estimate the tons required.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How many tons are in a cubic yard of gravel?</summary>
        <p>On average, a cubic yard of standard gravel weighs about 1.4 tons (or 2,800 pounds). However, this can vary slightly depending on the exact material, moisture content, and compaction. Pea gravel might weigh slightly less, while crushed stone or larger rock could be closer to 1.5 tons per cubic yard.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is the formula to calculate gravel volume?</summary>
        <p>The fundamental formula for gravel volume in cubic yards is: (Length in feet × Width in feet × Depth in feet) ÷ 27. Because depth is often measured in inches, you must first convert the inches to feet by dividing the inch measurement by 12 before performing the volume multiplication.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>How deep should I lay gravel?</summary>
        <p>The depth of gravel depends heavily on the application. For standard footpaths, 2 to 3 inches is usually sufficient. For driveways supporting standard vehicles, a minimum of 4 to 6 inches is recommended. For areas accommodating heavy equipment or large trucks, you may need a deeper base ranging from 8 to 12 inches.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Does the type of gravel affect the total weight?</summary>
        <p>Yes, different types of gravel and aggregates have varying densities. For example, crushed stone (like #57 stone) typically weighs around 1.35 to 1.4 tons per cubic yard, whereas dense-graded base (like crusher run or item 4) can weigh up to 1.5 tons per cubic yard due to the presence of stone dust that fills the voids.</p>
      </details>
    </section>
  </div>

  <script is:inline>
    const inputs = ['length', 'width', 'depth', 'lengthUnit', 'widthUnit', 'depthUnit', 'materialType'];
    const els = {};

    inputs.forEach(id => {
      els[id] = document.getElementById(id);
      els[id].addEventListener('input', calculateGravel);
      els[id].addEventListener('change', calculateGravel);
    });

    const results = {
      volumeYards: document.getElementById('volumeYards'),
      weightTons: document.getElementById('weightTons'),
      volumeMeters: document.getElementById('volumeMeters'),
      weightKg: document.getElementById('weightKg')
    };

    const errors = {
      length: document.getElementById('lengthError'),
      width: document.getElementById('widthError'),
      depth: document.getElementById('depthError')
    };

    function convertToMeters(val, unit) {
      if (unit === 'ft') return val * 0.3048;
      if (unit === 'm') return val;
      if (unit === 'in') return val * 0.0254;
      if (unit === 'cm') return val * 0.01;
      return 0;
    }

    function calculateGravel() {
      const lengthStr = els.length.value;
      const widthStr = els.width.value;
      const depthStr = els.depth.value;

      const length = parseFloat(lengthStr);
      const width = parseFloat(widthStr);
      const depth = parseFloat(depthStr);

      let hasError = false;

      if (isNaN(length) || length <= 0) { errors.length.style.display = 'block'; hasError = true; }
      else { errors.length.style.display = 'none'; }

      if (isNaN(width) || width <= 0) { errors.width.style.display = 'block'; hasError = true; }
      else { errors.width.style.display = 'none'; }

      if (isNaN(depth) || depth <= 0) { errors.depth.style.display = 'block'; hasError = true; }
      else { errors.depth.style.display = 'none'; }

      if (hasError) {
        results.volumeYards.textContent = '--';
        results.weightTons.textContent = '--';
        results.volumeMeters.textContent = '--';
        results.weightKg.textContent = '--';
        return;
      }

      const lengthMeters = convertToMeters(length, els.lengthUnit.value);
      const widthMeters = convertToMeters(width, els.widthUnit.value);
      const depthMeters = convertToMeters(depth, els.depthUnit.value);

      const volumeMeters3 = lengthMeters * widthMeters * depthMeters;
      const volumeYards3 = volumeMeters3 * 1.30795; // 1 m3 = 1.30795 yd3

      const densityTonsPerYd3 = parseFloat(els.materialType.value) || 1.4;
      const weightTons = volumeYards3 * densityTonsPerYd3;
      const weightKg = weightTons * 907.185; // 1 US ton = 907.185 kg

      const formatter = new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', { maximumFractionDigits: 2 });

      results.volumeYards.textContent = formatter.format(volumeYards3);
      results.weightTons.textContent = formatter.format(weightTons);
      results.volumeMeters.textContent = formatter.format(volumeMeters3);
      results.weightKg.textContent = formatter.format(weightKg);
    }

    // Initial calculation
    calculateGravel();
  </script>

  <style is:inline>
    .page-content { max-width: 900px; margin: 0 auto; padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .hero { text-align: center; padding: 3rem 0 2rem; }
    .hero h1 { font-size: 2.2rem; font-weight: 800; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .subtitle { color: var(--text-secondary); font-size: 1.1rem; }

    .calculator-container { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 12px; padding: 2rem; margin: 2rem 0; display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 2rem;}

    @media (min-width: 768px) {
      .calculator-container { flex-direction: row; align-items: stretch; }
      .calc-grid { flex: 1; border-right: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding-right: 2rem; }
      .results-area { flex: 1; display: flex; flex-direction: column; justify-content: center; padding-left: 2rem;}
    }

    .calc-grid { display: grid; gap: 1.5rem; }
    .input-group { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 0.5rem; }
    .input-group label { font-weight: 600; font-size: 0.95rem; }

    .input-with-unit { display: flex; gap: 0.5rem; }
    .input-with-unit input { flex: 2; }
    .input-with-unit select { flex: 1; min-width: 100px; }

    input, select { background: var(--bg-color); color: var(--text-primary); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); padding: 0.75rem 1rem; border-radius: 8px; width: 100%; font-size: 1rem; transition: border-color 0.2s, box-shadow 0.2s; }
    input:focus, select:focus { outline: none; border-color: var(--accent-color); box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 20%, transparent); }

    .error-msg { color: #ef4444; font-size: 0.85rem; display: none; margin-top: 0.25rem; }

    .results-area { display: flex; flex-direction: column; gap: 1rem; }

    .result-card { background: color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 10%, transparent); border: 1px solid color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent-color) 30%, transparent); border-radius: 12px; padding: 1.5rem; text-align: center; }
    .primary-result { padding: 2rem 1.5rem; }
    .result-label { font-size: 0.9rem; font-weight: 600; color: var(--text-secondary); text-transform: uppercase; letter-spacing: 0.05em; margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .result-value { font-size: 3rem; font-weight: 800; color: var(--accent-color); line-height: 1; }

    .secondary-results { display: grid; grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr; gap: 1rem; }
    .small-result { padding: 1rem; background: var(--bg-color); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .small-result .result-label { font-size: 0.75rem; margin-bottom: 0.25rem; }
    .result-value-sm { font-size: 1.5rem; font-weight: 700; color: var(--text-primary); }

    .explainer { margin-top: 3rem; line-height: 1.7; }
    .explainer h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 700; margin: 2rem 0 1rem; }
    .explainer h3 { font-size: 1.4rem; font-weight: 600; margin: 1.5rem 0 0.75rem; }
    .explainer p { margin-bottom: 1rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .explainer ul { margin-bottom: 1.5rem; padding-left: 1.5rem; color: var(--text-secondary); }
    .explainer li { margin-bottom: 0.5rem; }
    .explainer a { color: var(--accent-color); text-decoration: none; font-weight: 600; }
    .explainer a:hover { text-decoration: underline; }

    .formula-box { background: var(--card-bg); border: 1px solid var(--border-color); border-radius: 8px; padding: 1.25rem; margin: 1.5rem 0; font-family: monospace; font-size: 1.1rem; text-align: center; color: var(--accent-color); overflow-x: auto; }

    .faq-section { margin-top: 4rem; }
    .faq-section h2 { font-size: 1.8rem; font-weight: 700; margin-bottom: 1.5rem; }
    .faq-section details { margin: 1rem 0; padding: 1.25rem; background: var(--card-bg); border-radius: 8px; border: 1px solid var(--border-color); }
    .faq-section summary { font-weight: 600; cursor: pointer; font-size: 1.1rem; list-style-position: outside; margin-left: 0.5rem; }
    .faq-section details p { margin-top: 1rem; margin-bottom: 0; color: var(--text-secondary); line-height: 1.6; }
  </style>
</SiteLayout>